我是上班族。
I'm an office worker.

我在政府机关做事。
I work for the government.

很高兴见到你。
I'm happy to meet you.

我喜欢你的幽默感。
I like your sense of humor.

很高兴再次见到你。
I'm glad to see you again.

我会打电话给你。
I'll call you.

我想睡/散步。
I feel like sleeping/taking a walk.

我想吃点东西。
I want something to eat.

我需要你的帮助。
I need your help.

我想和你谈一下。
I would like to talk to you for a minute.

我有很多问题。
I have a lot of problems.

我希望我们的梦想成真。
I hope our dream come true.

我期待见到你。
I'm looking forward to seeing you.

我应该节食/涨工资。
I'm supposed to go on a diet/get a raise.

听说你要结婚了，恭喜！
I heard that you're getting married. Congratulations.

我了解你的意思。
I see what you mean.

我不能这么做。
I can't do this.

让我解释迟到的理由。
Let me explain why I was late.

咱们喝点啤酒什么的。
Let's have a beer or something.

你们的办公室在哪里？
Where is your office?

你的计划是什么？
What is your plan?

这家店什么时候结束营业？
When is the store closing?

你肯定你九点能来吗？
Are you sure you can come by at nine?

我可以十点过后再回家吗？
Am I allowed to stay out past 10?

会议原定了两个小时，不过现在还没结束。
The meeting was scheduled for two hours, but it is not over yet.

汤姆的生日就在这个星期。
Tom's birthday is this week.

你要不要看/坐一会儿呢？
Would you care to see it/sit down for a while?

星期五能不能请你替我个班/你能帮我吗/你能告诉我到那里怎么走吗？
Can you cover for me on Friday/help me/tell me how to get there?

能否请你帮我个忙？
Could you do me a big favor?

他对疯狂英语很着迷。
He is crazy about Crazy English.

你能想象他买那车花了多少钱吗？
Can you imagine how much he paid for that car?

你能相信我买了一台电视机吗？ 25美元？
Can you believe that I bought a TV for $25?

你知道他有外遇了吗？/欺骗他的妻子吗？
Did you know he was having an affair/cheating on his wife?

玛丽所有的钱是怎么赚到的？
How did Mary make all of her money?

你的约会怎么样？
How was your date?

你跟你的新上司处得如何？
How are you doing with your new boss?

我该如何告诉他这个坏消息？
How should I tell him the bad news?

你赚了多少钱？
How much money did you make?

出国要多少钱？
How much money does it cost to go abroad?

到你家要多久？
How long will it take to get to your house?

你在这里多久了？
How long have you been here?

好/漂亮/冷/有趣/愚蠢/无聊/有趣。
How nice/pretty/cold/funny/stupid/boring/interesting.

出去吃晚餐如何？
How about going out for dinner?

很遗憾，你没有得到那份工作
I'm sorry that you didn't get the job.

我恐怕这事不会成的。
I'm afraid that it's not going to work out.

我想我能来。
I guess I could come over.

在办公室里抽烟可以吗？
Is it okay to smoke in the office?

有点刺激。
It was kind of exciting.

我知道你想要什么。
I know what you want.

这就是你不想回家的原因吗？
Is that why you don't want to go home?

我很肯定我们可以帮你做成一笔好交易。
I'm sure we can get you a great/good deal.

你愿意帮我写报告吗？
Would you help me with the report?

我不知道他是世界上最有钱的人。
I didn't know he was the richest person in the world.

我必须先问一下我的老板/老婆。
I'll have to ask my boss/wife first.

这么说来，我认为你是不同意。
I take it you don't agree.

我曾试着减肥，但是毫无效果。
I tried losing weight, but nothing worked.

那么早起来没有任何意义。
It doesn't make any sense to get up so early.

讲一口流利的英语需要多年的刻苦操练。
It took years of hard work to speak good English.

感觉好像春天到了/我以前来过这里。
It feels like spring/I've been here before.

我在想他们是不是能办得到。
I wonder if they can make it.

今天不像昨天那么冷/热。
It's not as cold/hot as it was yesterday.

困扰我的不是他的工作，而是他的态度。
It's not his work that bothers me; it's his attitude.

听起来你好像蛮喜欢的。
It sounds like you enjoyed it.

我觉得他好像想要回家。
It seems to me that he would like to go back home.

看起来很漂亮。
It looks very nice.

一切都在掌握之中吗？
Is everything under control?

我以为你的表现会更好。
I thought you could do a better job.


